
                                            It is unclear what caused Sunday night's blaze which broke out in a ward.
                                         CAPE TOWN - A man has died in a fire at Groote Schuur Hospital. It is unclear what caused Sunday night's blaze which broke out in a ward. The victim was a patient. Fire and rescue services' Theo Layne: "The damage to the ward was one bed and bedside table. The incident was handed over to the police for their investigation. No other injuries were reported."